2.4.24  11:07 pm   i recently got a job making videos, which i like doing. the job is great, my boss is great, and the pay is also great. so everything is great, except that in order to do it i have to communicate a lot with people that i don't know very well. i am very bad at this, and it stresses me out a lot. so i feel stressed about this job even though i like almost every aspect of it. i'm not considering quitting or anything - it's only going to be for about a year anyway, it's very stable, and i need the money. i'm just thinking that in the future, i shouldn't make my hobbies myjob, unless i'm just working for myself. is this reasonable? maybe after awhile i'll get used to the communication parts of the job, but still, it's really stressful for me i'm also slightly worried that this job might set me on a career path of solely making videos, which isn't really something i want to do. is that a valid concern? i don't really know if those questions are really real, i just wanted someone to tell me whether or not i was freaking out for no reason. so, am i freaking out for no reason?
